Devlog 2025-10-23 (Ubuntu 24.04 system LLVM + shim removal)

  - Toolchain & CI
      - Bumped the minimum system requirement to LLVM/Clang 20 on Ubuntu 24.04; libclang-cpp20 is built with the C++23 libstdc++ ABI, so the generator can stay on the default C++23 dialect without compatibility shims.
      - Documented reliance on Kitware's `cmake` APT repo (>= 4.1) because the stock 24.04 cmake (3.28) no longer satisfies `cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.31)`.
      - Validated Fedora 41 runners using system packages only. `dnf install clang clang-devel clang-tools-extra llvm-devel fmt-devel zlib-ng-compat-devel libunwind-devel libcurl-devel libffi-devel libxml2-devel ninja-build` plus `pip install cmake` (for 4.x) let `gentest_codegen` build and run its unit tests under Clang 19 with C++23 and no shim.
  - Tools
      - Dropped `match_finder_compat.h` and `match_finder_shim.cpp`; `gentest_codegen` now constructs `clang::ast_matchers::MatchFinder` directly.
      - Restored the generator target to `cxx_std_23`.

Devlog 2025-10-20 (Clang 18 ABI guard and Fedora CI)

  - Tools
      - Updated `cmake/GentestCodegen.cmake` to wrap generator invocations with a `cmake -E env LD_LIBRARY_PATH=...` launcher when the bundled Terminfo shim is active. This ensures the shim wins lookup precedence for every suite, matching the behaviour of our new tests.
      - Added `tools/src/match_finder_compat.h` and `tools/src/match_finder_shim.cpp`. The shim compiles as C++17 and calls the mangled `clang::ast_matchers::MatchFinder` constructor directly, sidestepping the `std::optional` ABI change that caused clang-18 libclang-cpp to segfault under C++23.
      - `MatchFinderHolder` now owns placement storage inside `main.cpp`, keeping lifetime management explicit.
      - `match_finder_shim.cpp` is tagged with `-std=c++17` so it links against the old libstdc++ ABI. This relies on the constructorâ€™s Itanium mangled name; bumping LLVM/Clang may require updating that symbol, and the helper forfeits C++23 optional optimisations in that TU.
      - `tools/CMakeLists.txt` caches whether the shim is in play and its output directory, so downstream custom commands can reuse it.
  - Verification
      - `cmake --build --preset=debug --target gentest_codegen`
      - `ctest --test-dir build/debug-fedora --output-on-failure`
      - `DOCKER_HOST=unix:///run/user/$(id -u)/podman/podman.sock act -j fedora -P ubuntu-22.04=ghcr.io/catthehacker/ubuntu:act-22.04 -P ubuntu-24.04=ghcr.io/catthehacker/ubuntu:act-24.04 --pull=false`
